	   <tr><td colspan=2>i see alot of folks talking about Totemic armor for shaman. I looked at this armor, and its nice to have the balanced stats, but I am a shaman and want WISDOM.<br><br>Banded Gauntlets&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>AC: +7  <br>Weight: 4.0 <br><br>Imbued Northman Ring Gauntlets (Tribunal) <br>AC: +9 Str: +1 Wis: +2 Cold Resist: +2  <br>Weight: 5.0 <br><br>Totemic Gauntlets   <br>LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM  <br>AC: +11 Int: +5 Cold Resist: +5  <br>Weight: 2.8 <br><br>I use the Gauntlets here as examples 2 points of ac are good on the totemic, but even for trade skills that int doesn't help. There are a total of 8 pieces of totemic armor only a couple of which have wisdom.  All armor slots can be filled with Imbued Northman. <br><br>13 armor slots each giving +2 wisdom is a 24 point increase to wisdom. Each piece is 2 points better than the same banded which is a nice ac boost. Northman weighs 1 more than the same banded, but it also gives 1 str, end result you are no more incumbered by it than banded and can do a bit more damage due to the added str. <br><br>Total Stats:<br>Imbued Northman Ringmail: 126 ac, 13 str, 26 wis, 26 cold. Much more focused for the shaman and a better AC. <br><br>Totemic Armor: 102 AC, 5 str, 5 sta, 5 dex, 5 agi, 5 wis, 5 int, 5 cha, 5 cold, 5 magic, 5 disease, 5 poison, 5 fire. Nice and balanced.<br><br>Add to this an Imbued Northman Kite Shield (Tribunal)   <br>MAGIC ITEM  <br>AC: +10 Wis: +3 Cold Resist: +5 HP: +4  <br>Weight: 10.0 <br> <br>And 2 of these<br>Imbued Northman Mace (Triblnal)   <br>Damage: 9<br>Delay: 36 <br>Ratio: 4 Average<br>Range: 40 <br>Sta: +4 Wis: +2  <br>Weight: 8.5 <br>Weapon Skill: One Hand Blunt <br>Inventory Slot: Either Melee<br>***Can be equipped in the range slot ***<br> <br>With the add on of shield and maces we now have:<br>136 ac, 13 str, 36 wis, 8 sta, 4 hp, 31 cold.<br><br>I'll leave it to you to decide, but for myself I went with Imbued Northman, and still have most of it in my 40s. I am gradually replacing it as I find items that improve the AC and wisdom.<br><br>Benadan Meatshield<br>43rd Shaman Vazaelle<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
